// Adversarial: Split Decision fires a SpawnBolts effect on cell destruction, splitting
// the bolt count each time a cell is cleared. Dense layout guarantees a high rate of cell
// destruction events — multiple cells can be destroyed in the same frame when the bolt clips
// a cluster, firing multiple simultaneous SpawnBolts requests. The adversarial risk: if
// simultaneous SpawnBolts requests from the same frame each spawn independently without
// respecting the bolt count ceiling, BoltCountReasonable fires. Prism breaker starts with
// multiple bolts, compounding the bolt-count pressure from Split Decision spawns — Prism's
// native bolt count plus Split Decision cascades must stay under max_bolt_count 32. Chaos 0.3
// keeps breaker movement moderate so the bolt reliably hits cell clusters. If spawned bolts
// from simultaneous destructions are not properly sequenced through the spawn queue, entity
// lifecycle corruption causes NoEntityLeaks or NaN propagation from uninitialized bolt state.
// Stress: 32 runs to explore different Dense layout destruction cluster orderings.
(
    breaker: "Prism",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.3)),
    max_frames: 3000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltCountReasonable, NoEntityLeaks, BoltInBounds, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    invariant_params: (max_bolt_count: 32),
    allow_early_end: false,
    stress: (runs: 4, parallelism: 4),
    seed: 4507,
    chip_selections: ["Split Decision"],
)
